<前言><![CDATA[]]></前言>
<法規內容>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 1</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These regulations are enacted in accordance with the provisions of Paragraph 4, Article 36 of the Satellite Broadcasting Act.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 2</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[The term“Duration of Programs”in the provisions of Paragraph 4, Article 36 of the Satellite Broadcasting Act refers to a period from the onset of broadcasting program title, graphic, audio or text recognized as the start of the program to the moment before the broadcasting of next program title, graphic, audio or text recognized as the start of the following program.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 3</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[Advertisements may be broadcast three times in programs that air for up to 30 minutes, and six times in programs that air for up to 60 minutes. For programs that air for more than 60 minutes, the number of advertisements that may be broadcast shall be determined using the aforementioned principle.
For live events, advertisements may be broadcast at appropriate times.
“Advertisements” as referred to in Paragraph 1 include those that are broadcast before or after programs as well as those broadcast during programs.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
  <條文>
    <條號>Article 4</條號>
    <條文內容><![CDATA[These regulations shall come into force as of the date of promulgation.]]></條文內容>
  </條文>
</法規內容>
